The paper deals with deep convolutional neural networks (DCNNs) and their limitations in classifying partially occluded objects. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new architecture that integrates compositional models and DCNNs, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of differentiable compositional models, which is related to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed model's ability to localize occluders accurately, which is related to the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
